The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Dec. 12: Asked by states, tobacco may come under VAT as part of a compensation package for revenue loss due to the proposed phase out of central sales tax from April 1, 2007. The VAT panel today decided to ask the Centre for a compensation package, including powers on service tax, authority to levy VAT on imports and certain items under additional excise duty and relaxation on declared goods, to enable states to go for reduction in cst from next fiscal.

 Mumbai, Dec. 12: Sebi has directed the BSE to launch the corporate bond market reporting platform from January 1, 2007. It has been decided that BSE would be setting up and maintaining a corporate bond reporting platform ... with effect from January 1, 2007, a Sebi circular said.

 Mumbai, Dec. 12: The RBI today issued final guidelines covering important NBFCs and the banks relationships with them. According to the fresh guidelines, the banks exposure towards an NBFC has been capped at 10 per cent of their capital funds according to their last audited balance sheet and at 15 per cent in case of an NBFC involved in asset finance. 

 Hyderabad, Dec. 12: Satyam Computer Services has signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) with the Egypt government to set up a global development centre (GDC) in Giza. 

 New Delhi, Dec. 12: The government today ruled out any proposal to impose a ban on cement exports despite rising input costs putting pressure on cement prices.




